data.title: Beloved Tejano Legend Johnny Canales Passes Away
data.meta_description: Johnny Canales played a huge role in launching the career of legendary singer Selena.
data.text:
Many Tejano music lovers, El Pasoans included, are still mourning the loss of beloved Tejano legend Johnny Canales who passed away at the age of 76 last week.

A post was shared on Canales’ Facebook page that read:

"He was more than just a beloved husband, father, TV host, musician, and entertainer; he was a beacon of hope and joy for countless people.”

Johnny Canales & Selena Quintanilla

Canales is known for many things but for many Selena fans he is best known for his influential TV show, "The Johnny Canales Show," which played a huge role in launching the career of legendary singer Selena.

According to those who knew Canales, his vibrant personality and unwavering commitment to promoting Latino music and culture have made him a beloved figure in the industry.

"His infectious charisma and dedication to promoting Latino music and culture left a large mark on the world. Johnny's spirit will continue to live on through the countless lives he touched and the legacy he built."

A Tejano Music Icon That Will Never Be Forgotten

In the weeks leading up to his passing, Canales' family had shared updates about his grave illness, preparing fans and loved ones for this heartbreaking moment.

His death leaves a void in the hearts of many, but his contributions to Tejano music and the cultural tapestry of the Latino community will not be forgotten.

As the community comes to terms with this loss, the legacy of Johnny Canales stands as a testament to his life's work.

His show, music, and personality will continue to inspire future generations, ensuring that his influence endures.
